    "description": "The strategy is a rules based seasonal sector rotation that seeks to exploit recurring consumer demand and risk appetite patterns by overweighting US Consumer Cyclical equities during the year end through early spring window and holding the broad US equity market outside that window. The investable universe is US listed equities classified as Consumer Cyclical and priced above 5 dollars, with SPY used as the default market exposure.\n\nDecisions are made daily using fundamental sector classificati",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a rules based seasonal sector rotation that seeks to exploit recurring consumer demand and risk appetite patterns by overweighting US Consumer Cyclical equities during the year end through early spring window and holding the broad US equity market outside that window. The investable universe is US listed equities classified as Consumer Cyclical and priced above 5 dollars, with SPY used as the default market exposure.\n\nDecisions are made daily using fundamental sector classifications and daily price data, but the primary regime switch is calendar month based: in November through March the portfolio exits SPY and allocates equally across all currently eligible Consumer Cyclical stocks; in April through October it liquidates the cyclical basket and moves to 100 percent SPY. Position sizing is equal weight across selected cyclicals and fully invested at all times, so realized risk is driven by the number of constituents and sector concentration in the seasonal window. The intended alpha source is the seasonal return premium of Consumer Cyclical stocks versus the market, captured via deterministic timing and broad cross sectional diversification within the sector.",
